    <text id="A9200T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>In this letter to his cousin Virginia (also Enos's sister-in-law), J. W. writes
                    of his experiences in battle, mentioning the death of Captain Anderson and the
                    wounds of Jemmie Hanger and Jake Cox.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Paid 5 cents<lb/>Miss Virginia G. McCormick<lb/>Greenville Augusta Co Va
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1861-12-14">December 14, 1861</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><orig reg="Dear">Dare</orig> cousin</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I received my box the 12 I was <orig reg="very">vary</orig> glad to <orig
                        reg="get">git</orig> it I <orig reg="would">wood</orig> of <orig
                        reg="written">ritten</orig> yesterday but yesterday morning before sun up
                        <orig reg="the">they</orig> yankees came on <orig reg="us">ous</orig>
                    <orig reg="They">thay</orig> had <orig reg="us">ous</orig>
                    <orig reg="very">vary</orig>
                    <orig reg="near">neir</orig>
                    <orig reg="surrounded">serrounded</orig>
                    <orig reg="There">the</orig> was three 1000 yankees and about 14,100 of our men
                        <orig reg="We">wey</orig> had <orig reg="two">tow</orig> fights the yankees
                        <orig reg="divided">devied</orig> and went <orig reg="two">tow</orig> ways
                    our Regiment was in the ditches I was in <orig reg="front">frount</orig> of the
                    battle the <orig reg="whole">hole</orig> time the yankees had the <orig
                        reg="advantage">advantedg</orig> of our men <orig reg="they">thay</orig> got
                    in the tree tops behind logs and behind stumps so that we <orig reg="could"
                    >cood</orig> not see them when <add hand="h1" place="inline">
                        <orig reg="we">wey</orig>
                    </add>
                    <orig reg="would">wod</orig> look over the bank <orig reg="they">thay</orig>
                    <orig reg="would">wod</orig> shoot at <orig reg="us">ous</orig> I was <orig
                        reg="very">vary</orig>
                    <orig reg="near">neare</orig> give out when i got to the ditches it was the
                    first time I had <orig reg="been">ben</orig> out <orig reg="any">eny</orig>
                    distance for <orig reg="some">soum</orig> time I had <add hand="h1"
                        place="inline">no</add>
                    <orig reg="orders">ordes</orig> to go but I went and took good <orig reg="aim"
                        >ame</orig> at the yankees but I <orig reg="can't">cat</orig> say that I
                        <orig reg="killed">kiled</orig>
                    <orig reg="any">eny</orig> the balls fell like <orig reg="hail">hale</orig> the
                    yankees <orig reg="killed">kiled</orig> a good <orig reg="many">meny</orig> of
                        <add hand="h1" place="inline">our</add>
                    <orig reg="officers">oficers</orig>
                    <orig reg="They">thay</orig>
                    <orig reg="killed">kiled</orig><pb n="2"/><abbr expan="Captain">Cap't</abbr>
                    <orig reg="Anderson">andison</orig> close at me <orig reg="There">the</orig> is
                    a good many <orig reg="killed">kiled</orig> on both sides <orig reg="There"
                    >the</orig> is more yankees <orig reg="killed">kiled</orig>
                    <orig reg="than">then</orig> is on our side but I <orig reg="can't">
                        <abbr expan="cannot">cant</abbr>
                    </orig> tell how <orig reg="many">meny</orig> is lost on our side we <orig
                        reg="fought">faugh</orig>
                    <del hand="h1">from</del> a bout 6 <orig reg="hours">hors</orig> and <orig
                        reg="half">hafe</orig>
                    <orig reg="There">the</orig>
                    <del hand="h1">ut</del> is none of our company <orig reg="hurt">hirt</orig>
                    Jemmie Hanger is a little better this morning he had a bad <orig reg="chill"
                        >chil</orig> last night Jake Cox is <orig reg="complaining"
                    >complaying</orig> the rest of the boys is well <orig reg="except">exsept</orig>
                    bad <orig reg="colds">cols</orig>
                    <del hand="h1">I am a</del> I feel better this morning <orig reg="than"
                    >then</orig> I have felt for some time I have had <orig reg="something"
                    >southing</orig> like the <orig reg="neuralgia">neuralsia</orig> in my head I am
                        <orig reg="very">vary</orig> well <orig reg="pleased">please</orig> with my
                    shirts and pants I <orig reg="can't">
                        <abbr expan="cannot">cant</abbr>
                    </orig> tell <orig reg="whether">wether</orig> we will come to Staunton or not
                        <orig reg="They're">thery</orig> still <orig reg="talking">tawking</orig>
                    about it <orig reg="Please">plees</orig> let father have those <orig reg="shoes"
                        >shoos</orig> that I <orig reg="drew">drue</orig> in Staunton they are <orig
                        reg="too">tow</orig> large for me if <orig reg="there">the</orig> is <orig
                        reg="any">eny</orig>
                    <orig reg="passing">pasing</orig> to <orig reg="Midway">midway</orig>
                    <orig reg="please">plese</orig> send them to Mr <orig reg="Nelson's"
                    >nelson</orig> store I drew a <orig reg="pair">paire</orig> of <orig reg="shoes"
                        >shoos</orig> the <orig reg="shoes">shoos</orig> is good that I brought from
                    home nothing more at present <orig reg="only">oly</orig> remain your
                    affectionate Cousin until death</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>J W Campbell</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">
                        <name type="recipient">Virginia G MC</name>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
